{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c3f619dd-1f48-4526-a4e3-4bd50f5f3fbb","content":"Analyzing `.dmp` files isn't something I can do directly in this environment — dump analysis requires specialized tools like **WinDbg**, **Visual Studio**, or **dotnet-dump analyze**. Here's how you can do it:\n\n### Recommended approach\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nThen inside the interactive session:\n```\n> clrstack          # managed call stacks\n> pe                # print last exception\n> dumpheap -stat    # heap summary\n> threads           # list all threads\n```\n\n**Using WinDbg** (Windows):\n1. Open the `.dmp` file\n2. Load SOS: `.loadby sos clr` (Framework) or `.loadby sos coreclr` (.NET Core+)\n3. Run `!pe` (print exception), `!clrstack`, `!threads`\n\n### Quick triage checklist\n- `pe` → shows the exception type/message/stack trace\n- `clrstack -all` → shows what every managed thread was doing\n- `dumpheap -stat` → reveals possible memory issues\n\nWould you like more detailed guidance on any of these steps?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9031f53c-a2ba-4486-9df8-9767844fdb10","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it to find the root cause of a crash. Let me check if any of the available skills are relevant for this task.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files, not .dmp files\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs, not .dmp files\n\n\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - For capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n\nNone of the available skills can help with analyzing .dmp files, so I'll need to guide the user through the process directly.","outputTokens":515,"requestId":"418D:3F6047:62AC82D:6BF4BB5:69F164BE"},"id":"02267309-3c7a-46bb-b73a-1f2d00af6cf0","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:54:19.857Z","parentId":"ab039f43-fd6e-48db-9609-ef4174f1c394"}
